      </video>
      <h2 class="subtitle has-text-centered">
        <span class="dnerf">SkyEvents</span> enables robust 3D scene reconstruction across 
        <strong>4.5km flight trajectories</strong> by fusing RGB and Event streams.
      </h2>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container is-max-desktop">
    <div class="columns is-centered has-text-centered">
      <div class="column is-four-fifths">
        <h2 class="title is-3">Abstract</h2>
        <div class="content has-text-justified">
          <p>
            As a promising solution, bio-inspired event cameras exhibit robustness in extreme scenarios, 
            thanks to their high dynamic range and microsecond-level temporal resolution. 
            Nevertheless, dedicated event datasets specifically tailored for large-scale UAV 3D scene reconstruction remain limited. 
          </p>
          <p>
            To bridge this gap, we introduce <strong>SkyEvents</strong>, a pioneering large-scale event-enhanced UAV dataset 
            for 3D scene reconstruction, incorporating RGB, event, and LiDAR data. SkyEvents encompasses 
            <strong>22 sequences</strong>, spanning over <strong>8 hours</strong> of video, captured across a diverse set of 
            illumination conditions, scenarios, and flight altitudes. 
          </p>
          <p>
            To facilitate the event-based 3D scene reconstruction with SkyEvents, we propose the 
            <strong>Geometry-constrained Timestamp Alignment (GTA)</strong> module to align timestamps between 
            the event and RGB cameras. Furthermore, we introduce <strong>Region-wise Event Rendering (RER)</strong> 
            loss for supervising the rendering optimization. With SkyEvents, we aim to motivate and equip 
            researchers to advance large-scale 3D scene reconstruction in challenging environments.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="columns is-centered has-text-centered">
      <div class="column is-four-fifths">
        <h2 class="title is-3">Video Presentation</h2>
        <div class="publication-video">
          <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YOUR_VIDEO_ID?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0"
                  frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
</section>


<section class="section">
  <div class="container is-max-desktop">

    <div class="columns is-centered">
      <div class="column is-full-width">
        <h2 class="title is-3">Dataset Overview</h2>
        <div class="content has-text-justified">
          <p>
            The <strong>SkyEvents</strong> dataset features synchronized data from RGB cameras, Event cameras (Prophesee), and LiDAR.
            It covers urban, rural, and campus scenes under varying lighting conditions (day, night, sunset).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="content has-text-centered">
          <img src="./static/images/dataset_overview.png"
               class="interpolation-image"
               alt="Dataset Overview."/>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="columns is-centered">
      <div class="column is-full-width">
        <h2 class="title is-3">Methodology</h2>
        <div class="content has-text-justified">
          <p>
            We introduce two key components to handle the asynchronous nature of event data in 3D reconstruction:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Geometry-constrained Timestamp Alignment (GTA)</strong>: Ensures precise temporal alignment between event streams and RGB frames using geometric constraints from LiDAR ground truth.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Region-wise Event Rendering (RER) Loss</strong>: A novel loss function that optimizes the reconstruction by focusing on high-frequency regions captured by the event camera.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content has-text-centered">
          <img src="./static/images/method.png"
               class="interpolation-image"
               alt="Method Pipeline."/>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
</section>


